Angular JS is an open source JavaScript framework that is used to build web applications. It can be freely used, changed and shared by anyone.


Angular 7 is a JavaScript (actually a TypeScript based open-source full-stack web application) framework which makes you able to create reactive 
Single Page Applications (SPAs). Angular 7 is completely based on components.

AngularJS expressions can be written inside double braces: {{ expression }}.
AngularJS expressions can also be written inside a directive: ng-bind="expression".
 
<div ng-app="myApp" ng-controller="personCtrl"> 


var app = angular.module('myApp', []);     //
app.controller('personCtrl', function($scope)




);

